## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID. |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Errors if zero or more than one skill matches. |

This data source reads **both** custom skills and builtin
(MisterShell-managed) skills. Builtin skills (`is_builtin = true`) are read-only
and can only be read here — they cannot be created or managed as a resource.

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | AI skill integer ID. |
| `name` | Skill name. |
| `description` | Short purpose line shown in `list_skills` (may be empty). |
| `body` | Markdown platform-brief body, possibly containing Jinja2 variables. |
| `agent_types` | Set of agent type values the skill's discovery is restricted to, or empty if unrestricted. Values: `chat`, `background`, `builtin_chat`, `builtin_background`, `builtin_quick_action`, `builtin_session_assist`. |
| `resource_types` | Set of resource-type descriptor keys the skill's discovery is restricted to (a discovery filter, not an auth gate), or empty if unrestricted. |
| `is_enabled` | Whether the skill appears in `list_skills`. |
| `is_builtin` | Whether MisterShell manages this skill from its registry (read-only; only `is_enabled` is mutable for builtins). |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

For the full meaning of `agent_types` / `resource_types`, the omit-vs-empty-list
rule, and the list of builtin skills, see the
[`mistershell_ai_skill` resource](../resources/ai_skill.md) page.
